  ('split-stance-drop-in-start', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/acceleration_start_speed because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use before chase starts, lateral-to-sprint work, or sport-specific first-step sessions.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('band-resisted-first-step', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/acceleration_start_speed because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use early Output after unresisted starts; resistance must be light enough to preserve sprint mechanics.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('light-sled-10m-acceleration', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/acceleration_start_speed because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'After unresisted starts; keep load light enough for fast steps and full recovery.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('hill-sprint-acceleration', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/acceleration_start_speed because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use as an Output alternative when safe incline and full recovery are available.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('chase-reaction-sprint', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/reactive_agility_tumbling_output because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'After basic starts when athletes can handle competition without losing mechanics.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('lateral-open-step-to-sprint', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/deceleration_cod_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use in Output after linear starts, before more chaotic COD or reactive work.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('flying-10m-sprint', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/max_velocity_exposure because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Early Output on days where max speed is the priority, after mechanics and progressive build-ups.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
