  ('wicket-run-max-velocity', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/max_velocity_exposure because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use as a technical max-velocity exposure before free fly sprints or on rhythm-focused speed days.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('straight-leg-bounds-to-sprint', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/max_velocity_exposure because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use before upright sprinting with athletes who can keep contacts elastic and pelvis tall.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('fast-leg-cycle-drill', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Movement Intelligence/locomotion_sprint_mechanics because the athlete must learn posture, rhythm, and coordination before fatigue or high-output attempts.', 'Use before max velocity exposures; keep it technical, not exhaustive.', 'Most common misuse: rushing the drill or turning it into conditioning instead of using it to improve mechanics and readiness.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('progressive-build-up-sprint-30m', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/max_velocity_exposure because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use as a bridge from mechanics to fast sprinting or on lower-readiness speed days.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('curve-sprint-build-up', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/max_velocity_exposure because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use after straight-line build-ups once athletes can handle the bend without collapsing posture.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('dribble-build-to-sprint', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/max_velocity_exposure because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use after dribble runs and before flying sprints or wickets on max-velocity rhythm days.', 'Most common misuse: turning high-intent sprint reps into conditioning. Stop when timing, posture, or relaxation drops; do not place after fatigue-heavy lifting or circuits.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('pogo-jumps', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/elastic_stiffness_plyometric_rudiments because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use as a potentiation bridge or early Output plyometric; keep contact count low and crisp.', 'Most common misuse: chasing jump/contact volume until contacts get slow, loud, or painful. Keep contacts crisp and separate from fatigue conditioning.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('single-leg-pogo', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/elastic_stiffness_plyometric_rudiments because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use only after bilateral pogos are quiet and pain-free; low contacts per side.', 'Most common misuse: chasing jump/contact volume until contacts get slow, loud, or painful. Keep contacts crisp and separate from fatigue conditioning.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('alternating-bounds', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/elastic_stiffness_plyometric_rudiments because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use after low-level plyos and before/after short sprints when fresh.', 'Most common misuse: chasing jump/contact volume until contacts get slow, loud, or painful. Keep contacts crisp and separate from fatigue conditioning.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('single-leg-bounds', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/elastic_stiffness_plyometric_rudiments because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Advanced Output only, after acceleration or as a primary plyometric with full rest.', 'Most common misuse: chasing jump/contact volume until contacts get slow, loud, or painful. Keep contacts crisp and separate from fatigue conditioning.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('low-hurdle-hops', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/elastic_stiffness_plyometric_rudiments because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use as an Output plyometric only when pogos are quiet and athletes can rebound without collapsing.', 'Most common misuse: chasing jump/contact volume until contacts get slow, loud, or painful. Keep contacts crisp and separate from fatigue conditioning.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('drop-jump-reactive', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/elastic_stiffness_plyometric_rudiments because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Advanced Output only after landing mechanics and low-level hops are sound.', 'Most common misuse: chasing jump/contact volume until contacts get slow, loud, or painful. Keep contacts crisp and separate from fatigue conditioning.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('lateral-skater-bound-stick', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Resilience/landing_braking_control because it develops braking, control, or tissue tolerance after primary output work.', 'Use after Output or in Resilience; make the stick perfect before making it faster.', 'Most common misuse: chasing jump/contact volume until contacts get slow, loud, or painful. Keep contacts crisp and separate from fatigue conditioning.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('snap-down-to-stick', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Resilience/landing_braking_control because it develops braking, control, or tissue tolerance after primary output work.', 'Use before jumps as a low-level landing primer or after Output as braking resilience work.', 'Most common misuse: chasing jump/contact volume until contacts get slow, loud, or painful. Keep contacts crisp and separate from fatigue conditioning.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('countermovement-jump', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/jump_throw_explosive_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use early Output before heavy lifts or as a readiness/power marker.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('standing-broad-jump', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/jump_throw_explosive_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use early Output before starts or lower-body strength work.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('triple-broad-jump', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/jump_throw_explosive_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Advanced Output drill after standing broad jumps are stable and pain-free.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('med-ball-chest-pass', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/jump_throw_explosive_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Early Output before upper-body strength or sport-specific throwing/striking work.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('med-ball-scoop-toss', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/jump_throw_explosive_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Early Output before sprint starts or hinge-dominant strength work.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('med-ball-overhead-back-toss', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/jump_throw_explosive_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Early Output when space and safety are controlled; pair before lower-body power or acceleration starts.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('med-ball-rotational-shot-put', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/jump_throw_explosive_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Early Output after trunk activation; especially useful for throwing, striking, and rotational field athletes.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('med-ball-step-behind-rotational-throw', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Output/jump_throw_explosive_power because it is a freshness-sensitive speed-power drill: high intent, low volume, and full recovery are required for transfer.', 'Use after static rotational throws once spacing, sequencing, and wall safety are controlled.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('trap-bar-deadlift', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Capacity/hinge_posterior_chain_strength because it raises force or tissue capacity after speed has been expressed.', 'Capacity phase after sprint/output work; avoid heavy pulls before max speed exposure.', 'Most common misuse: loading so heavy or to failure that the athlete loses sprint quality later in the week or before Output in the same session.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('rear-foot-elevated-split-squat', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Capacity/squat_knee_dominant_strength because it raises force or tissue capacity after speed has been expressed.', 'Capacity phase after speed work; not as a pre-sprint fatigue drill.', 'Most common misuse: loading so heavy or to failure that the athlete loses sprint quality later in the week or before Output in the same session.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('romanian-deadlift', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Capacity/hinge_posterior_chain_strength because it raises force or tissue capacity after speed has been expressed.', 'Capacity phase after sprinting; use controlled tempo without excessive soreness before speed days.', 'Most common misuse: loading so heavy or to failure that the athlete loses sprint quality later in the week or before Output in the same session.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('heavy-sled-push-march', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Capacity/hinge_posterior_chain_strength because it raises force or tissue capacity after speed has been expressed.', 'Capacity phase after acceleration work; keep it strength-focused, not conditioning, unless placed in sustained capacity.', 'Most common misuse: loading so heavy or to failure that the athlete loses sprint quality later in the week or before Output in the same session.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('hang-power-clean-from-high-hang', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Capacity/hinge_posterior_chain_strength because it raises force or tissue capacity after speed has been expressed.', 'Capacity or power-support block after sprint Output; requires supervision and should not replace sprint exposure.', 'Most common misuse: using loads that are too heavy or reps that are too high, which turns quick release into slow strength endurance.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('nordic-hamstring-eccentric', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Resilience/slow_eccentric_isometric_joint_resilience because it develops braking, control, or tissue tolerance after primary output work.', 'Resilience or accessory slot after speed and strength; dose conservatively due to soreness potential.', 'Most common misuse: adding too much eccentric/control volume and creating soreness that compromises sprint exposures.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('seated-soleus-raise', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Capacity/tissue_capacity_isometric_eccentric_accessory because it raises force or tissue capacity after speed has been expressed.', 'Capacity or Resilience accessory after sprint/plyo work; not a pre-output burnout.', 'Most common misuse: loading so heavy or to failure that the athlete loses sprint quality later in the week or before Output in the same session.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.'),
  ('banded-hip-flexor-march', 'It targets the limiting qualities behind speed transfer: force direction, rapid stiffness, clean limb timing, and the ability to express force before fatigue changes mechanics.', 'Belongs in Prepare & Access/activate because it primes sprint-specific tissues and positions without stealing output from the main speed work.', 'Prepare & Access activation before A-march, wall drills, or starts; avoid fatiguing the hip flexors.', 'Most common misuse: rushing the drill or turning it into conditioning instead of using it to improve mechanics and readiness.', 'Scale by speed quality, landing/contact quality, range of motion, and tissue readiness. Regress first by reducing speed, amplitude, load, or reactive complexity.')
